{
  "circuit": {
    "description": "cshunt gate fixture: V1 sine (0.3V amp, 0V offset, 1kHz) -> R1=1k -> mid; D1(RS=10,IS=1e-14,N=1) mid->gnd mints a device-internal anode node (excluded from cshunt); R2=10k mid->gnd. Smooth sine keeps the diode in a gentle regime for bit-exact baseline. Transient run with .option cshunt proves external/netlist-only injection: in and mid get a shunt cap, the diode internal anode does not.",
